#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:2
msgid "Basic test configuration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:5
msgid "Command line options and configuration file settings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:7
msgid ""
"You can get help on command line options and values in INI-style "
"configurations files by using the general help option::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:10
msgid "py.test -h   # prints options _and_ config file settings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:12
msgid ""
"This will display command line and configuration file settings which were "
"registered by installed plugins."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:19
msgid "initialization: determining rootdir and inifile"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:23
msgid ""
"pytest determines a \"rootdir\" for each test run which depends on the "
"command line arguments (specified test files, paths) and on the existence of "
"inifiles.  The determined rootdir and ini-file are printed as part of the "
"pytest header.  The rootdir is used for constructing \"nodeids\" during "
"collection and may also be used by plugins to store project/testrun-specific "
"information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:30
msgid "Here is the algorithm which finds the rootdir from ``args``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:32
msgid "determine the common ancestor directory for the specified ``args``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:34
msgid ""
"look for ``pytest.ini``, ``tox.ini`` and ``setup.cfg`` files in the ancestor "
"directory and upwards.  If one is matched, it becomes the ini-file and its "
"directory becomes the rootdir.  An existing ``pytest.ini`` file will always "
"be considered a match whereas ``tox.ini`` and ``setup.cfg`` will only match "
"if they contain a ``[pytest]`` section."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:41
msgid ""
"if no ini-file was found, look for ``setup.py`` upwards from the common "
"ancestor directory to determine the ``rootdir``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:44
msgid ""
"if no ini-file and no ``setup.py`` was found, use the already determined "
"common ancestor as root directory.  This allows to work with pytest in "
"structures that are not part of a package and don't have any particular ini-"
"file configuration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:49
msgid ""
"Note that options from multiple ini-files candidates are never merged, the "
"first one wins (``pytest.ini`` always wins even if it does not contain a "
"``[pytest]`` section)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:53
msgid "The ``config`` object will subsequently carry these attributes:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:55
msgid "``config.rootdir``: the determined root directory, guaranteed to exist."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:57
msgid "``config.inifile``: the determined ini-file, may be ``None``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:59
msgid ""
"The rootdir is used a reference directory for constructing test addresses "
"(\"nodeids\") and can be used also by plugins for storing per-testrun "
"information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:63
msgid "Example::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:65
msgid "py.test path/to/testdir path/other/"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:67
msgid ""
"will determine the common ancestor as ``path`` and then check for ini-files "
"as follows::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:70
msgid ""
"# first look for pytest.ini files\n"
"path/pytest.ini\n"
"path/setup.cfg  # must also contain [pytest] section to match\n"
"path/tox.ini    # must also contain [pytest] section to match\n"
"pytest.ini\n"
"... # all the way down to the root\n"
"\n"
"# now look for setup.py\n"
"path/setup.py\n"
"setup.py\n"
"... # all the way down to the root"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:87
msgid "How to change command line options defaults"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:89
msgid ""
"It can be tedious to type the same series of command line options every time "
"you use ``pytest``.  For example, if you always want to see detailed info on "
"skipped and xfailed tests, as well as have terser \"dot\" progress output, "
"you can write it into a configuration file:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:94
msgid ""
"# content of pytest.ini\n"
"# (or tox.ini or setup.cfg)\n"
"[pytest]\n"
"addopts = -rsxX -q"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:101
msgid ""
"Alternatively, you can set a PYTEST_ADDOPTS environment variable to add "
"command line options while the environment is in use::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:104
msgid "export PYTEST_ADDOPTS=\"-rsxX -q\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:106
msgid "From now on, running ``pytest`` will add the specified options."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:111
msgid "Builtin configuration file options"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:115
msgid "Specifies a minimal pytest version required for running tests."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:117
msgid "minversion = 2.1  # will fail if we run with pytest-2.0"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:121
msgid ""
"Add the specified ``OPTS`` to the set of command line arguments as if they "
"had been specified by the user. Example: if you have this ini file content:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:124
msgid ""
"[pytest]\n"
"addopts = --maxfail=2 -rf  # exit after 2 failures, report fail info"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:129
msgid "issuing ``py.test test_hello.py`` actually means::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:131
msgid "py.test --maxfail=2 -rf test_hello.py"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:133
msgid "Default is to add no options."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:137
msgid ""
"Set the directory basename patterns to avoid when recursing for test "
"discovery.  The individual (fnmatch-style) patterns are applied to the "
"basename of a directory to decide if to recurse into it. Pattern matching "
"characters::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:142
msgid ""
"*       matches everything\n"
"?       matches any single character\n"
"[seq]   matches any character in seq\n"
"[!seq]  matches any char not in seq"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:147
msgid ""
"Default patterns are ``'.*', 'CVS', '_darcs', '{arch}', '*.egg'``. Setting a "
"``norecursedirs`` replaces the default.  Here is an example of how to avoid "
"certain directories:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:151
msgid ""
"# content of setup.cfg\n"
"[pytest]\n"
"norecursedirs = .svn _build tmp*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:157
msgid ""
"This would tell ``pytest`` to not look into typical subversion or sphinx-"
"build directories or into any ``tmp`` prefixed directory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:164
msgid ""
"Sets list of directories that should be searched for tests when no specific "
"directories, files or test ids are given in the command line when executing "
"pytest from the :ref:`rootdir <rootdir>` directory. Useful when all project "
"tests are in a known location to speed up test collection and to avoid "
"picking up undesired tests by accident."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:170
msgid ""
"# content of pytest.ini\n"
"[pytest]\n"
"testpaths = testing doc"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:176
msgid ""
"This tells pytest to only look for tests in ``testing`` and ``doc`` "
"directories when executing from the root directory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:181
msgid ""
"One or more Glob-style file patterns determining which python files are "
"considered as test modules."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:186
msgid ""
"One or more name prefixes or glob-style patterns determining which classes "
"are considered for test collection. Here is an example of how to collect "
"tests from classes that end in ``Suite``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:190
msgid ""
"# content of pytest.ini\n"
"[pytest]\n"
"python_classes = *Suite"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:196
msgid ""
"Note that ``unittest.TestCase`` derived classes are always collected "
"regardless of this option, as ``unittest``'s own collection framework is "
"used to collect those tests."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:202
msgid ""
"One or more name prefixes or glob-patterns determining which test functions "
"and methods are considered tests. Here is an example of how to collect test "
"functions and methods that end in ``_test``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:206
msgid ""
"# content of pytest.ini\n"
"[pytest]\n"
"python_functions = *_test"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:212
msgid ""
"Note that this has no effect on methods that live on a ``unittest ."
"TestCase`` derived class, as ``unittest``'s own collection framework is used "
"to collect those tests."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:216
msgid "See :ref:`change naming conventions` for more detailed examples."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:220
msgid ""
"One or more doctest flag names from the standard ``doctest`` module. :doc:"
"`See how py.test handles doctests <doctest>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/customize.rst:225
msgid ""
"Sets a directory where search upwards for ``conftest.py`` files stops. By "
"default, pytest will stop searching for ``conftest.py`` files upwards from "
"``pytest.ini``/``tox.ini``/``setup.cfg`` of the project if any, or up to the "
"file-system root."
msgstr ""
